@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Create ticket (auto-classify)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets?auto_classify=true
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "D1",
  "customer_email": "d1@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Demo One",
  "subject": "Critical crash in production",
  "description": "App crashes when saving settings",
  "category": "other",
  "priority": "medium",
  "status": "new",
  "metadata": { "source": "api", "browser": "Chrome", "device_type": "desktop" }
}

### List tickets filtered
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?category=technical_issue&priority=urgent

### Bulk import (JSON)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "format": "json",
  "content": "[{\"customer_id\":\"J1\",\"customer_email\":\"j1@example.com\",\"customer_name\":\"J1\",\"subject\":\"Login\",\"description\":\"Cannot login due to 2FA\",\"category\":\"other\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"status\":\"new\",\"metadata\":{\"source\":\"api\",\"device_type\":\"desktop\"}}]",
  "auto_classify": true
}

### Auto-classify specific ticket
# Replace :id with a real ID from previous responses
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/:id/auto-classify
